description: TEHRAN - The Iranian Foreign Minister Abbas Araghchi told his Iraqi counterpart Fuad Hussein in a telephone conversation on Monday night that the United States’ illegal sanctions against Iran's oil industry are baseless and lack credibility.
title: Iran to Iraq: US illegal sanctions against on Iran’s oil industry lack credibility

description: Just days before Turkey’s main opposition party was set to select its next presidential candidate, the leading contender, Istanbul Mayor Ekrem Imamoglu, was arrested and jailed, effectively removing him from the race. In this brazen act of political suppression, the Turkish government has taken a momentous step toward full-fledged autocracy.
title: Turkey is now a full-blown autocracy

description: Tesla's downward spiral is turning into a rout, with its share of European electric car sales falling by 58 percent in the first two months of this year, dropping from 18.4 percent in 2024 to 7.7 percent for the same period this year, according to data from JATO Dynamics, an auto consulting firm.
title: Tesla’s Europe sales collapse as anti-Musk backlash grows

description: TEHRAN - Foreign Minister Abbas Araghchi asserted on Monday that he is quite sure that no country dares to attack Iran because the country is in “complete readiness”.
title: No one can even think of attack on Iran, FM asserts

description: BEIJING- A group of foreign journalists participating in a media exchange program organized by the China International Press Communication Center (CIPCC) are visiting Hainan Province.
title: Hainan to become global aircraft maintenance center

description: Wang Yi,  a member of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee and Foreign Minister, met ? on 14 March 2025 with Deputy Foreign Minister Ryabkov Sergey Alexeevich of the Russian Federation and Deputy Foreign Minister Kazem Gharibabadi of the Islamic Republic of Iran?who attended the Beijing Meeting between China, Russia and Iran, and proposed the following five points on the proper settlement of the Iranian nuclear issue.
title: China’s five-point proposition on the Iran nuclear issue

description: TEHRAN- The daily production of gasoline in Iran’s Persian Gulf Star Refinery (PGSR) has risen by four million liters in the second half of the past Iranian calendar year (March 20-Septemeber 20, 2024), the managing director of Persian Gulf Star Oil Company announced.
title: PGSR’s daily gasoline production up 4m liters in H2

description: TEHRAN- The minister of energy announced the implementation of 14 mega projects by the Energy Ministry to address electricity imbalance in the country in the new Iranian calendar year (started on March 21).
title: Energy Ministry to implement 14 mega projects to tackle energy imbalance

description: TEHRAN – Iran exported non-oil commodities valued at $6.4 billion to Turkey during the 11-month period from March 20, 2024-February 18, 2025, the head of the Islamic Republic of Iran Customs Administration (IRICA) announced.
title: Iran exports non-oil goods worth $6.4b to Turkey in 11 months
